column6: Hacking with great people with the support of awesome mentors
There is no rush, or deadlines, i just code in my own speed. There is no pressure.
The mentors, attendans and the location. The workshops too.
column7: I think that a brief explanation about NodeJS and some use cases would have been very interesting too.

column6: The event was very practical and focused on coding. As a programmer I understand the best way to learn a technology is to work directly with it rather than watch slides. The event materials were very good.
column7: Since the event takes 3 hours, perhaps a coding demo of 5-10 minutes can be done to learn Node specifics

column6: There was a very relaxed vibe, perfect for working. Also being able to learn at each one's own pace thanks to the Workshopper modules.
It was an event guided to developers for developers

column7: A little bit more introduction to node
